HOOKS
=====

This directory contains post-receive hooks that allow you to set up a
hair-shirted remote-build framework. Using this, you can trigger builds as
follows:

	$ git push straylight:autobuild HEAD:rootfs

Please see https://t0technology.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DH/pages/640778241
for more information.

Setting Up
----------

1. On the build server, set up a bare repository endpoint that will receive
   your push triggers:

   $ git clone --bare git@github.com:t0/crs-yocto.git autobuild

2. On the build server, install the post-receive hook:

   $ cd autobuild
   $ git show main:hooks/post-receive > hooks/post-receive
   $ chmod 755 hooks/post-receive

3. On your development machine, try it out:

   $ source setenv.sh
   $ build-rootfs

   Please see the Confluence page linked at the top of this document for more
   information.
